<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1465284" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/APC-L0G0.jpg?resize=600%2C400&#038;ssl=1" alt="APC chieftains laud members in Enugu North for setting aside differences" width="600" height="400" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/APC-L0G0.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/APC-L0G0.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/APC-L0G0.jpg?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/APC-L0G0.jpg?resize=260%2C173&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/APC-L0G0.jpg?resize=195%2C130&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/APC-L0G0.jpg?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> A group of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) supporters in Kungurki Ward in Kaura Namoda Local Government Area (LGA) of Zamfara has defected to All Progressives Congress (APC). The group announced its defection at a ceremony on Wednesday in Sabongarin Kaura in Kaura-Namoda. Speaking on behalf of the group, Malam Bala Ayuba said that the former PDP members under three different groups decided to leave the party for APC. “We decided to defect to APC because we are not satisfied with the current PDP leadership in the state. “We have not recorded achievements for almost over a year of the PDP led government in the state. “The current PDP leadership has not performed well especially in the area of addressing security challenges in the state, ” Ayuba said. Also speaking, Malama Balkisu Abdullahi, the former PDP ward women leader said that they decided to join APC because of neglect by PDP. “The PDP led government in the state has forgotten us, we have not recorded any progress under its leadership. “We have been supporting PDP for over 16 years, unfortunately, the party forgot us when it came to power. “On behalf of the entire PDP women in Kungurki ward, l announce our defection to APC,” Abdullahi said. Receiving the defectors, Alhaji Umaru Isiyaka, APC Kaura-Namoda LGA Chairman, commended the defectors for joining APC. “We are happy with this development, indicated that thousands of PDP members from Kungurki ward are joining our great party today, ” Isiyaku said. He called on all APC members in the state to remain united and peaceful for development of the state. He commended the state APC caretaker Chairman, Alhaji Lawal Liman and the state party leader, Alhaji Abdul’aziz Yari for living up to expectations. Vanguard News Nigeria Eight out of the 14 Local Government Area Council chairmen on the platform of the  All Progressives Congress (APC), in Zamfara, have announced their defection to the ruling Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). February 8, 2020 In "Politics" A lawmaker representing Maru North Constituency in Zamfara State House of Assembly, Alhaji Salisu Yakubu, has defected from All Progressive Congress (APC) to the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). December 31, 2014 In "News" Zamfara-based political pressure group, Concerned Citizens of Zamfara, has debunked claims that 41 chieftains of All Progressives Congress, APC, including relatives of former Governor Abdul'aziz Yari, defected in Talata Mafara Local Government Area, LGA. March 1, 2020 In "News"